cable_ref: LA PAZ 0246, AND LA PAZ 244 SUMMARY: BOLIVIA CURRENTLY EXPERIENCING SERIOUS FLOUR SHORTAGE WITH SERIOUS POLITICAL IMPLICATIONS FOR GOVERNMENT. ALTHOUGH PRECISE REASONS FOR CURRENT PROBLEM DIFFICULT TO UNTANGLE, BASIC CAUSE APPEARS TO BE FAILURE OF ARGENTINA TO FULFILL COMMITMENTS FOR FLOUR DELIVERIES. THIS HAS BEEN COUPLED IN RECENT WEEKS WITH GREATER THAN USUAL TRANSPORTATION DIFFICULTIES FROM PORTS, ESPECIALLY PERUVIAN RAIL STRIKE WHICH SLOWED MOVEMENT OF PL-480 WHEAT FROM MATARANI. SITUATION MAY IMPROVE THIS WEEK AS RAILROADS NOW MOVING WHEAT AT NORMAL PACE AND SMALL QUANTITY OF FOUR DUE TO ARRIVE FROM ARGENTINA, BUT SHORTAGES LIKELY TO REAPPEAR SINCE STOCKS WILL CONTINUE LOW AND SCARCITIES HAVE INDUCED SPECULATION AND CREATION BLACK MARKET. END SUMMARY.

cable_subject: PL-480 TITLE I LIMA FOR AGATT
cable_ref: STATE 092148 AND LA PAZ A-023. SUMMARY: WE ESTIMATE THAT EVEN IF PRESENT COMMERCIAL WHEAT/FLOUR IMPORT ARRANGEMENTS IMPLEMENTED BOLIVIA WILL HAVE SUPPLY GAP OF ABOUT 40,000 M.T. OF WHEAT WHICH SHOULD BE MET BY PL-480. WE BELIEVE FURTHER AGREEMENT JUSTIFIED ON BASIS POOR BALANCE OF PAYMENTS PROSPECTS FOR 1975, AS INTEGRAL ELEMENT USG ASSISTANCE STRATEGY FOR AGRRICULTURE SECTOR AND OTHER DEVELOPMENT SECTORS IN WHICH USG DIRECTING ITS EFFORTS. WE ALSO SEE POSSIBILITY THAT PL-480 GENERATIONS MIGHT BE USED TO HELP FINANCE LOCAL CURRENCY COSTS LATER PHASES RECONSTRUCTION FLOOD DAMAGED AREAS. WE JUDGE PL-480 HAS HIGH GOB PRIORITY, IS POLITICALLY IMPORTANT AND THAT USG HAS RESPONSIBILITY TO USE THIS FLEXIBLE TOOL IN HELPING SOLVE BOLIVIA'S GRAIN SUPPLY PROBLEM AND TO AVOID JOLTING CHANGE FROM SUBSTANTIAL WHEAT CREDIT PROGRAM TO NO WHEAT CREDIT PROGRAM AT ALL. END SUMMARY:

ART. 4 IF STUDIES SHOW THEIR TECHNICAL AND ECONOMIC FEASIBILITY (A) BOLIVIAN GOVERNMENT (GOBO) IS COMMITTED TO SELL AVERAGE 240 MILLION CUBIC FEET OF NATURAL GAS TO BRAZIL FOR 20 YEARS ON TERMS AND CONDITIONS (INCLUDING PRICE WHICH CAN BE ADJUSTED EVERY SIX MONTHS IN ACCORDANCE WITH INTERNATIONAL MARKET PRICE) TO BE ESTABLISHED IN CONTRACT BETWEEN PETROLEO BRASILEIRO S.A. (PETROBRAS) AND YACIMIENTOS PETROLIFEROS FISCALES BOLIVIANOS (YPFB); (B) BRAZILIAN GOVERNMENT (GOBR) IS COMMITTED TO COOPERATE IN IMPLEMENTATION OF PROJECTS AND INFRASTRUCTURE NEEDED FOR GAS PIPELINES AND INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT POLE AS SET OUT IN ARTS. 2 AND 3; (C) GOBR IS COMMITTED TO GUARANTEE MARKET FOR PRODUCTS OF BOLIVIAN INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT POLE IN ACCORDANCE WITH TERMS OF ANNEX II OF ACT WHICH SPELLS OUT IN DETAIL PERCENT OF PRODUCTION OF EACH PLANT WHICH BRAZIL AGREES TO TAKE AS MINIMUM AND CUSTOMS AND INTERNAL TAXES THAT WILL APPLY. 2. (ART.3) GOBO WILL PRESENT TO GOBR STUDY ON GAS RESERVES CERTIFYING SUFFICIENT SUPPLIES TO MEET 240 MILLION CUBIC FEET PER DAY FOR 20 YEARS COMMITMENT TO GOBR. GOBO WILL DO STUDIES FOR GAS PIPELINES WITH SUFFICIENT CAPACITY TO SUPPLY BOLIVIAN INDUSTRIES TO BE ESTABLISHED PLUS COMMITMENT TO BRAZIL. GOBR WILL DO STUDIES FOR GAS PIPELINE FROM BORDER TO BRAZILIAN CONSUMPTION POINTS. 3. (ART.2) GOBO AND GOBR WILL COOPERATE TO DO STUDIES FOR (A) STEEL COMPLEX WITH CAPACITY TO PRODUCE ANNUALLY 900,000 M.T. SPONGE IRON AND STEEL AND LAMINATIONS EQUIVALENT TO 500,000 M.T. STEEL; (B) NITROGENOUS FERTILIZER PLANT WITH UREA PRODUCTION CAPACITY OF 1,000 M.T. PER DAY; (C) CEMENT PLANT WITH CAPACITY OF 1,000 M.T. PER DAY AND (D) INFRASTRUCTURE FOR DEVELOPMENT POLE. 4. (ART.1) GOBO AND GOBR AGREE TO CARRY OUT ASAP ESTABLISHMENT OF PLANTS REFEREED TO IN PRECEDING PARA PLUS POWER PLANT. BOLIVIA DISPOSED TO IMPLEMENT (CONCRETAR) GAS SALE TO BRAZIL "IN CONJUNCTION WITH" UNCLASSIFIED UNCLASSIFIED PAGE 03 LA PAZ 03356 01 OF 02 232250Z ESTABLISHMENT OF DEVELOPMENT POLE. 5. ART.5 GOBR WILL FINANCE GOBO STUDIES REFERRED TO IN ART. II(PRECEDING PARA) IN AMOUNT UP TO US$ 10 MILLION, 5 PERCENT INTEREST, 3 YEARS GRACE, 15 YEARS TOTAL TERM. LOAN AGREEMENT TO BE SIGNED WITHIN 30 DAYS FROM SIGNING ACT LOAN PROCEEDS FREELY DISPOSABLE AND CONVERTIBLE. 6. (ART 2.) GOBR AND GOBO WILL ESTABLISH BOLIVIAN- Declassified/Released US Department of State EO Systematic Review 30 JUN 2005 Declassified/Released US Department of State EO Systematic Review 30 JUN 2005 BRAZILIAN ECONOMIC AND TECHNICAL COOPERATION COMMITTEE TO COORDINATE IMPLEMENTATION OF ACT. 7. GOBR IS COMMITTED TO (A) FINANCE ALL OF GOBO PURCHASES OF BRAZILIAN GOODS AND SERVICES FOR PROJECTS DESCRIBED IN ARTS. II AND III AT INTEREST RATES AND TERMS EQUAL TO BEST GRANTED BY GOBR TO OTHER COUNTRIES AT TIME REQUESTED; (B) GUARANTEE FINANCING OF UP TO HALF OF PURCHASES OF GOODS AND SERVICES GOBO MAY MAKE IN THIRD COUNTRIES FOR PROJECTS DESCRIBED IN ART.
